workflow

Class WorkflowElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • core.Entity
      • workflow.WorkflowElement
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Consultation, HealthService, Installation, Transportation, Triage

    public abstract class WorkflowElement
extends Entity
    This is an abstract class which represents every workflow element in the Emergency Department. A workflow element represent a special task. It has a waiting queue of patients and apply the treatment to the first one. It also has a tasks queue for tasks which has to be terminated in the future. It has a cost. It may take a random time given by a probability distribution.
    Author:
    Quentin

      • getNextTask

        public Task getNextTask()
        This method return the next task to be executed by the service The priority in the tasks is the following:
        • Treat the next severe patient (L1 or L2)
        • Treat the next light patient (L3 to L5)
        • End the treatment of the next patient in the tasks queue
        Returns:
        The next task to be done by the installation service
